<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <p xml:id="PN343-intro">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. paraṇar.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en">  
      </p>
    </div> 
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PN343">
<l>mīṉoṭuttu neṟkuvaii</l>
<l>micaiyampiyiṉ maṉaimaṟukkuntu</l>
<l>maṉaikkuvaiiya kaṟimūṭaiyāṟ</l>
<l>kaliccummaiya karaikalakkuṟuntu</l>
<l>kalantanta poṟparicaṅ</l>
<l>kaḻittōṇiyāṟ karaicērkkuntu</l>
<l>malaittāramuṅ kaṭaṟṟāramun</l>
<l>talaippeytu varunarkkīyum</l>
<l>puṉalaṅ kaḷḷiṉ polantārk kuṭṭuvaṉ</l>
<l>muḻaṅkukaṭaṉ muḻaviṉ mucuṟi yaṉṉa</l>
<l>nalañcāl viḻupporuḷ paṇintuvantu koṭuppiṉum</l>
<l>puraiya rallōr varaiyala ḷivaḷeṉat</l>
<l>tantaiyuṅ koṭāa ṉāyiṉ vantōr</l>
<l>vāyppaṭa viṟutta vēṇi yāyiṭai</l>
<l>varuntiṉṟu kollō tāṉē paruntuyirt</l>
<l>tiṭaimatiṟ cēkkum puricaip</l>
<l>paṭaimayaṅ kāriṭai neṭuna lūrē.</l>
</lg>
<lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Like Mucuṟi with drums [and] the thundering ocean</l>
<l>of Kuṭṭuvaṉ with a golden garland, [his] toddy a flood,</l>
<l>where, have bartered fish [and] heaped paddy,</l>
<l>houses refuse high little boats,</l>
<l>where the shores are busy, burdened with clamour</l>
<l>by vessels with pepper that are heaped in the houses,</l>
<l>where they bring ashore by the backwater boats</l>
<l>the gold objects brought by ship,</l>
<l>and where they meet strangers [and] give them</l>
<l>goods from the mountains and goods from the sea</l>
<l>if, even when he came humbly [and] gives excellent wealth superb in quality [like that],</l>
<l>saying “she will not marry one who is not great”</l>
<l>[her] father did not give her, in between</l>
<l>the ladders placed in order to find a way [in] by those who have come,</l>
<l>did it suffer,</l>
<l>the long good town with difficult ways confused by weapons</l>
<l>[and] fortifications where kites sigh [and] rest on the inner walls?</l>
</lg>
